{
  "info": {
    "name": "ISO 20022 Payment Initiation — Switch Gateway",
    "description": "Postman collection for banks initiating cross-border payments through the Switch gateway.\n\n## Authentication\n- **Production**: mTLS (client certificate) — configure in Postman Settings → Certificates\n  - Host: `localhost`, Port: `8443`, CRT: `deploy/docker/client-bank-a-cert.pem`, KEY: `deploy/docker/client-bank-a-key.pem`\n\n## Content Negotiation\nThe gateway supports both JSON and ISO 20022 XML (pacs.008) requests.\n\n## ISO 20022 Messages\n- **camt.003.001.07** — Account lookup (POST /payments/lookup)\n- **pacs.008.001.08** — Payment instruction (POST /payments)\n- **pacs.002.001.10** — Payment status report (retrieved via GET /payments/{id} or delivered via callback)\n\n## Async Processing\nPayments are processed asynchronously:\n1. **POST /payments** returns `202 Accepted` immediately with `{\"id\":\"...\",\"status\":\"RECEIVED\",\"iso_status\":\"RCVD\"}`\n2. The saga runs in the background → `COMMITTED` or `ABORTED`\n3. Poll **GET /payments/{id}** for the final status\n4. A **pacs.002 callback** is POSTed to the bank's configured `callback_url` when processing completes",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://localhost:8443",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "source_bic",
      "value": "BANKUS33",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "source_account",
      "value": "US123456789",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "participant_id",
      "value": "bank-a",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
